Police Command in Ogun State says the remaining four pastors of the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG) abducted on Thursday have been rescued from the kidnappers’ den. Earlier today, the Police Spokesman, Abimbola Oyeyemi said the only female among the victims, Mrs Ibelegbo Chidinma, was rescued unhurt. Few hours later, Oyeyemi, in a one paragraph statement, disclosed that four other captives have equally been rescued unhurt. “UPDATE ON KIDNAP CASE: The remaining four victims have been rescued unhurt by men of Ogun state police command. Details shortly,” Oyeyemi said. The captives were on their way to Redeem camp for the Ministers’ conference when they were abducted at J3/J4 Area of Benin – Ijebu – Ode – Sagamu expressway. Oyeyemi had said that efforts were in top gear to rescue other captives but expressed concerns that the abductors kept the victims in separate locations, adding that and they were changing their locations within the forest. BREAKING!!! RCCG Pastors' Kidnap: Police rescue one as abductors change locations Police confirm abduction of 5 persons in Ogun 5 kidnappers killed in Ogun Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin